import React from 'react';
import { Button, Paper, Grid, Typography } from '@material-ui/core';

export const Home = () => {
  return (
    <Grid>
      <Grid container spacing={3}>
        <Grid item xs={12}>
          <Paper elevation={2}>
            <Typography variant="h4" gutterBottom>
              Headings & Text
            </Typography>
            <Typography variant="body1" gutterBottom>
              A sample of body text.
            </Typography>
          </Paper>
        </Grid>
        <Grid item xs={12}>
          <Paper elevation={2}>
            <Typography variant="h4" gutterBottom>
              Buttons
            </Typography>
            <Button variant="contained">Contained</Button>
          </Paper>
        </Grid>
        <Grid item xs={12}>
          <Paper elevation={2}>
            <Typography variant="h4" gutterBottom>
              Controls
            </Typography>
          </Paper>
        </Grid>
        <Grid item xs={12}>
          <Paper elevation={2}>
            <Typography variant="h4" gutterBottom>
              Modal
            </Typography>
          </Paper>
        </Grid>
      </Grid>
    </Grid>
  );
};
